### Tomcat Monitoring API Requests
### Test file for Tomcat Thread Pool Monitoring endpoints

### 1. Get Tomcat Metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tomcat/metrics
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Get Detailed Tomcat Information
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tomcat/details
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get Tomcat Status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tomcat/status
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Real-time Tomcat Metrics Stream (SSE)
# Note: This is a Server-Sent Events endpoint that streams continuously
# Open this in a browser or use a tool that supports SSE
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tomcat/stream
Accept: text/event-stream

###

### 5. Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tomcat/health
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Access Tomcat Dashboard (Browser)
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8080/dashboard/tomcat
GET http://localhost:8080/dashboard/tomcat

###

### 7. Generate Load - Sync Endpoint (to see Tomcat threads in action)
# Run multiple of these simultaneously to see thread pool activity
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/1

###

### 8. Generate Load - Async Endpoint (compare thread usage)
# Run multiple of these simultaneously and compare with sync
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/1

###

### 9. Check Actuator Metrics (if enabled)
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/metrics
Accept: application/json

###

### 10. Check Actuator Health
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

###

